H.B. 306
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 5, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40198-NO-38A
Short Title: Affordable Housing for Local Employees. (Local)
Sponsors: Representative Pickett.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT AUTHORIZING THE TOWNS OF BLOWING ROCK AND BOONE, WATAUGA
3 COUNTY, AND THE WATAUGA COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION TO
4 CONSTRUCT AND PROVIDE AFFORDABLE HOUSING FOR TOWN AND COUNTY
5 EMPLOYEES AND PUBLIC SCHOOL TEACHERS.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding G.S. 66-58, G.S. 115C-518, Article 12 of Chapter
8 160A of the General Statutes, or any other provision of law, the Towns of Blowing Rock and
9 Boone, Watauga County, and the Watauga County Board of Education (hereinafter "local
10 government unit") are authorized to do all of the following:
11 (1) Either separately or through a partnership, joint venture, land trust, or other
12 similar entity, construct and provide affordable housing for local government
13 unit employees on property owned by the unit.
14 (2) Convey property owned by the local government unit to a partnership, joint
15 venture, land trust, or similar entity for the purpose of constructing, providing,
16 or maintaining affordable housing for unit employees. A unit shall not convey
17 to a partnership, joint venture, land trust, or any other entity any property that
18 was acquired through the exercise of eminent domain on or after the date this
19 act becomes law.
20 (3) Contract with any person, partnership, corporation, or other business entity to
21 finance, construct, or maintain affordable housing for local government unit
22 employees.
23 (4) Rent or sell affordable housing units for residential use exclusively to local
24 government unit employees. A unit may establish reasonable rents or sales
25 prices, charge below-market rates, offer below-market financing, and place
26 reasonable restrictions and buyback provisions on the resale of the affordable
27 housing units.
28 SECTION 2. Any affordable housing units constructed pursuant to the provisions of
29 this act shall comply with all applicable building codes, zoning ordinances, and any other State
30 and local regulations related to the construction of residential homes.
31 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*DRH40198-NO-38A*

